OL,3,CJersey's Consumer Council calls for
OL,4,Cutility regulator for island
OL,6,FCarl Walker is the chair of Jersey's
OL,7,Fconsumer council and says there is too
OL,8,Fmuch contradicting information around
OL,9,Fprices. He says: "The difficulty we've
OL,10,Fgot from a consumer perspective is
OL,11,Fthat there is no real transparency. In
OL,12,Fone island they're (customers) being
OL,13,Ftold the global situation means prices
OL,14,Fmust come down and in our island we're
OL,15,Fbeing told the same global situation
OL,16,Fmeans prices must go up.
